Class MessageQueue<MessageType>

java.lang.Object
  com.larkwoodlabs.channels.MessageQueue<MessageType>
Type Parameters:
MessageType - The message object type.
All Implemented Interfaces:
MessageInput<MessageType>, MessageOutput<MessageType>, MessagePipe<MessageType>
public final class MessageQueue<MessageType>
extends Object
implements MessagePipe<MessageType>

A message pipe that buffers messages in a fixed-size, blocking queue. Typically used to connect an InputChannelPipe to an OutputChannelPipe to provide a means for passing messages from one thread to another thread.

Author:
Greg Bumgardner (gbumgard)

Constructor Detail

MessageQueue

public MessageQueue(int capacity)
Constructs a message queue with the specified maximum capacity. When the queue reaches maximum capacity, the send(Object, int) method will block until a message is removed from the queue, or the send timeout is reached.

Parameters:
capacity - The maximum number of messages that can be held in the queue.
